---
const stages = [
  { n: '01', title: 'Business Strategy', q: 'What are we trying to achieve?' },
  { n: '02', title: 'Operating Model', q: 'How should the business operate?', active: true },
  { n: '03', title: 'Business Capabilities', q: 'What capabilities create value?' },
  { n: '04', title: 'Business Solutions', q: 'How do we enable them?' },
  { n: '05', title: 'Delivery', q: "What's the most effective way?" },
];
---

<section class="section section--paper-2 opmodel">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow teal">Definition</p>
      <h2>The Business Operating Model</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Every organization has one, whether it's documented or not. It's how work flows, how decisions get
        made, how information moves and, ultimately, how the organization creates value.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="opmodel__grid">
      <div class="opmodel__prose reveal">
        <p>
          Most operating models are never consciously designed. They evolve. Products launch, teams grow,
          departments reorganize, software is purchased, spreadsheets appear and manual workarounds harden
          into permanent process. Before long the organization is adapting to its systems rather than the
          reverse.
        </p>
        <blockquote class="opmodel__pull">
          "If we were designing this business from scratch today, how would we want it to operate?"
        </blockquote>
        <p>
          Software isn't the operating model — it's one way of enabling it. The goal isn't more software.
          It's the right capabilities, built the most effective way.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="opmodel__flow reveal" role="list" aria-label="Every technology decision should trace back to a business strategy">
      <p class="opmodel__flow-label">Every technology decision should trace back to a business strategy</p>
      <div class="flow">
        {stages.map((s, i) => (
          <>
            <div class={`flow__step${s.active ? ' flow__step--active' : ''}`} role="listitem">
              <span class="flow__n">{s.n}</span>
              <span class="flow__title">{s.title}</span>
              <span class="flow__q">{s.q}</span>
            </div>
            {i < stages.length - 1 && <span class="flow__arrow" aria-hidden="true">›</span>}
          </>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="opmodel__split reveal">
      <div class="split-card split-card--teal">
        <h3><span class="split-dot" style="background:var(--teal)"></span>Differentiating</h3>
        <p>Capabilities that create competitive advantage. Often worth designing specifically for your organization.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="split-card split-card--coral">
        <h3><span class="split-dot" style="background:var(--coral)"></span>Commodity</h3>
        <p>Payroll, accounting, identity, payments. Already solved extremely well — buy, don't rebuild.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="opmodel__foot reveal">
      Knowing which is which is a primary outcome of the review — and it makes technology a consequence of
      strategy rather than the starting point.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .opmodel__grid { margin-bottom: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem); }
  .opmodel__prose { max-width: 68ch; }
  .opmodel__prose p { color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-size: 1.08rem; }
  .opmodel__pull {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--coral);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin: 1.75rem 0;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2.6vw, 1.55rem);
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  /* Strategy → delivery flow strip */
  .opmodel__flow {
    background: var(--ink);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 2.5rem);
    margin-bottom: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
  }
  .opmodel__flow-label {
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--teal-bright);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .flow {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
    align-items: stretch;
    gap: 0.25rem;
  }
  .flow__step {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1.25rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background: var(--ink-3);
    color: var(--text-on-dark);
  }
  .flow__step--active { background: var(--teal); }
  .flow__n { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.85rem; opacity: 0.7; }
  .flow__title { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.15; }
  .flow__q { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--text-on-dark-muted); }
  .flow__step--active .flow__q { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); }
  .flow__arrow { display: none; color: var(--text-on-dark-muted); align-self: center; font-size: 1.5rem; }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .flow {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0.6rem;
    }
    .flow__step { flex-direction: row; align-items: baseline; text-align: left; gap: 0.75rem; }
    .flow__step .flow__q { margin-left: auto; text-align: right; }
  }

  /* Differentiating vs commodity */
  .opmodel__split {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  .split-card {
    background: var(--paper);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .split-card h3 { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.6rem; font-size: 1.35rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .split-dot { width: 12px; height: 12px; border-radius: 50%; flex: none; }
  .split-card p { color: var(--text-muted); }

  .opmodel__foot {
    text-align: center;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2.4vw, 1.3rem);
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin-inline: auto;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  @media (max-width: 620px) {
    .opmodel__split { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
